      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): deduplicate tool_use blocks across legacy assistant messages",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nLegacy transcript rows (`transcript_entry_id IS NULL`) can carry duplicate `tool_call_id` groups across multiple assistant messages. On every context assembly cycle, `repairToolUseResultPairing` drops the corresponding tool results as duplicates and reports them, inflating context and spamming warnings.\n\nThe fix adds a preprocessing step inside `repairToolUseResultPairing` that tracks seen `tool_call_id`s globally and skips assistant messages whose every `tool_call_id` was already produced by an earlier turn.\n\nFixes #94829\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Repeated `\"sanitizeToolUseResultPairing dropped N duplicate assistant tool_use block(s)\"` warnings from the lossless-claw context engine during assembly.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node.js, Vitest test suite\n- **Repo**: openclaw/openclaw at `upstream/main` (844f405 + this fix)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after fix**:\n\n```bash\npnpm test -- src/agents/session-transcript-repair.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  57 passed (57)\n```\n\nAll 57 tests pass including 2 new tests that specifically cover legacy null-transcript duplicate scenarios.\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: When `repairToolUseResultPairing` encounters an assistant message whose every `tool_call_id` is already tracked from an earlier turn, it skips the duplicate message instead of processing it and then reporting a duplicate tool-result drop.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end lossless-claw plugin integration (plugin is external). The fix is in the shared core function that the plugin calls.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `session-transcript-repair.test.ts`: 57/57 passed (2 new tests)\n- `embedded-agent-runner.guard.test.ts`: 6/6 passed (regression)\n- `tool-result-context-guard.test.ts`: 45/45 passed (regression)\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`No`)\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- The preprocessing step runs inside `repairToolUseResultPairing`, which is called from multiple paths (HTTP, RPC, context assembly, replay history). Any regression in the dedup logic could silently drop valid assistant messages.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- The dedup only triggers when `toolCalls.every(...)` — i.e., ALL tool_call_ids in a message are already seen. This is a very narrow condition. Non-duplicate and mixed messages pass through unchanged.\n- 106 existing regression tests across 3 test files confirm no behavioral change for non-duplicate inputs.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
